  "body": "### Description\n\nProviders such as https://github.com/IdentityPython/SATOSA do not return a JWK set with the keys whose properties contain `kid` or the certificate thumbprint. Tokens issued from such providers (possibly federated from interposed SAML providers) may have no `kid` or the cert thumbprint either.\r\n\r\n`quarkus-oidc` rejects such tokens because it does find a matching key.\r\n\r\nHowever if the incoming token has no `kid` or `x5t` and the single key in a JWK set has no these properties set either then, since the set contains a single key only, there is no ambiguity and this single key should be tried for the token verification.\r\n\r\n(`smallrye-jwt` also supports this edge case)\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nIf JWK set has only a single key without either `kid` or `x5t`/`x5c` then this key should be recorded and used but only if the token has no `kid`/`x5t`",
